ar right. Bringing Bakhtin into dialogue with key developments in contemporary politics, this book is a must-read for anyone interested in the Trump phenomenon, American politics, and populism.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 4aDemokratie. 4aPopulismus. 4aSocial Media. 4aTrump, Donald. 4aUSA. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / American Government / General.2bisacsh  aDemocracy.  aPopulism.  aSocial Media.  aTrump, Donald.1 aGanesh, Bharath, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut0 cEPUBz97831112422930 cprintz978311123799240uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9783111238135zOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783111238135zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783111238135/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-GOA